result.terraform:
terraform {
  required_version = ">= 1.5.0"
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

locals {
  app_name = "app08"
  common_tags = {
    Application = local.app_name
    ManagedBy   = "data-gen-pipeline"
  }
}

resource "aws_launch_template" "compute" {
  name_prefix   = "${local.app_name}-compute-"
  image_id      = "ami-0c55b159cbfafe1f0"
  instance_type = "m5.large"

  tag_specifications {
    resource_type = "instance"
    tags = merge(local.common_tags, { Tier = "compute" })
  }
}

resource "aws_autoscaling_group" "compute" {
  name                = "${local.app_name}-compute-asg"
  min_size            = 8
  max_size            = 12
  desired_capacity    = 8
  vpc_zone_identifier = ["subnet-placeholder-a", "subnet-placeholder-b"]

  launch_template {
    id      = aws_launch_template.compute.id
    version = "$Latest"
  }

  tag {
    key                 = "Application"
    value               = local.app_name
    propagate_at_launch = true
  }
  tag {
    key                 = "Tier"
    value               = "compute"
    propagate_at_launch = true
  }
}

resource "aws_db_instance" "database_primary" {
  identifier              = "${local.app_name}-db-primary"
  engine                  = "postgres"
  engine_version          = "16.1"
  instance_class          = "db.r6g.xlarge"
  allocated_storage       = 500
  storage_encrypted       = true
  skip_final_snapshot     = true
  username                = "appuser"
  password                = "placeholder-rotate-in-prod"
  publicly_accessible     = false

  tags = merge(local.common_tags, { Tier = "database", Role = "primary" })
}




resource "aws_security_group_rule" "compute_to_database" {
  description       = "app08: compute tier queries database tier"
  type              = "ingress"
  from_port         = 5432
  to_port           = 5432
  protocol          = "tcp"
  security_group_id = "sg-placeholder-database"
  source_security_group_id = "sg-placeholder-compute"
}

synthesis.specific_change:
Action 1: Add covering indexes on the 6 slow queries (evidence_ref=34):

1a. Cart lookup (820ms P95, 6M executions): `SELECT c.*, ci.* FROM carts c JOIN cart_items ci ON ci.cart_id = c.id WHERE c.user_id = ?`
  — CREATE INDEX idx_carts_user_id_id ON carts (user_id, id);
  — CREATE INDEX idx_cart_items_cart_id ON cart_items (cart_id);

1b. Inventory join (680ms P95, 3.5M executions): `SELECT i.*, p.* FROM inventory i JOIN products p ON p.id = i.product_id WHERE i.warehouse_id IN (...)`
  — CREATE INDEX idx_inventory_warehouse_product ON inventory (warehouse_id, product_id);

1c. Pricing lookup (580ms P95, 4M executions): `SELECT * FROM pricing WHERE product_id = ? AND region = ? AND valid_from <= NOW() AND valid_to > NOW() ORDER BY priority DESC`
  — CREATE INDEX idx_pricing_product_region_validity_priority ON pricing (product_id, region, valid_from, valid_to, priority);

1d. Payment providers (440ms P95, 1.3M executions): `SELECT pp.* FROM payment_providers pp WHERE pp.country = ? AND pp.is_active = TRUE ORDER BY pp.priority`
  — CREATE INDEX idx_payment_providers_country_active_priority ON payment_providers (country, is_active, priority);

1e. Order history (510ms P95, 504K executions): `SELECT o.*, oi.* FROM orders o JOIN order_items oi ON oi.order_id = o.id WHERE o.user_id = ? ORDER BY o.created_at DESC LIMIT 50`
  — CREATE INDEX idx_orders_user_created_id ON orders (user_id, created_at, id);
  — CREATE INDEX idx_order_items_order_id ON order_items (order_id);

1f. Fulfillment (380ms P95, 672K executions): `SELECT f.* FROM fulfillment f WHERE f.order_id = ? AND f.status IN ('pending','allocated')`
  — CREATE INDEX idx_fulfillment_order_status ON fulfillment (order_id, status);

Action 2: Add 2 read replicas (db.r6g.xlarge) with R/W splitting (evidence_ref=51, evidence_ref=22):
  — Scale from 1 read replica to 3 read replicas (add 2 db.r6g.xlarge instances).
  — Enable R/W splitting at the application connection layer so read-heavy checkout queries are distributed across replicas instead of hitting the primary.
  — Cost delta: +$2,200/month (2 × db.r6g.xlarge at $1,100/month each). Current database tier cost: $2,200/month. New database tier cost: $4,400/month. New total monthly cost: $8,600/month.

Do NOT change compute:
  — The ASG fleet of 8× m5.large (min=8, max=12, target-tracking) is correctly sized. CPU P95 at 67% and memory P95 at 64.4% during peak hours are within healthy bands. Application latency will drop to 180–240ms once the database bottleneck is resolved, without any compute scaling. Do NOT increase ASG max, upsize instance class, or adjust scaling thresholds.

